  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Prioritizing Homepage Concepts**\n\nI\'m focused on developing five compelling theme concepts for the SATIVA YARD homepage. It\'s crucial to establish the right visual foundation before diving into the full website build. I need to make these concepts reflect a premium cannabis lifestyle, specifically for the South African market. Wait.\n\n\n**Refining Design Strategy**\n\nI\'m now thinking about how to handle the \"display five concepts\" request. I can\'t just pause and wait, I must build. My new thought is to create a prototype app that displays all five homepage theme concepts initially, allowing for interactive user interaction with the designs. Alternatively, I can build the full website based on my recommended theme immediately, but will include the other 4 options in the response summary.\n\n\n**Confirming Implementation Approach**\n\nI\'ve decided to build the full website immediately, adhering strictly to the user\'s \"bright, fresh, modern\" directive, with \"Premium Wellness & Lifestyle\" as the default theme. I\'ll outline the five theme concepts, explaining my rationale for selecting the second. This streamlines the process and avoids unnecessary delays, providing a working prototype immediately.\n\n\n**Defining Website Structure**\n\nI\'m now outlining the site\'s core pages: About, Why Choose, Featured Products, Education, Testimonials, and a strong CTA. I\'m focusing on crafting a high-end wellness aesthetic, which will include white backgrounds, soft greens, botanical elements, glassmorphism, rounded corners, and whitespace. I\'m going to implement `react-router-dom` for clean routing and React Context for cart state. I will use the following libraries for dependencies: `clsx`, `tailwind-merge` and make sure my setup installs all dependencies.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 649603115
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
