  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Success and Next Steps**\n\nThe build completed successfully, and I followed the prompt\'s instructions precisely, ensuring compliance with all constraints (bright colors, modern UI, WhatsApp integration). The functional cart mapping to WhatsApp checkout is now implemented. I\'m now focusing on the next task, as specified in the prompt.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the SATIVA YARD e-commerce application. As requested, here are the **FIVE Homepage Theme Concepts** structured around your brand goals, followed by the prototype implementation of the strongest recommendation.\n\n### 5 Homepage Theme Concepts\n\n**Theme Option 1: Modern Cannabis Dispensary**\n* **Visual Direction**: Clinical, highly structured, and precise. Looks more like a modern pharmacy interface.\n* **Colors**: Pure White, Clinical Blue-Green, and Light Grey.\n* **Typography**: Highly legible, geometric sans-serif (e.g., Roboto).\n* **Vibe**: Safe, legally compliant, and medical-first.\n\n**Theme Option 2: Premium Wellness & Lifestyle (\360\237\221\221 Recommended)**\n* **Visual Direction**: Resembles a high-end D2C wellness/skincare brand (Apple-level clean styling). Features sweeping soft backgrounds, glassmorphism cards, and lifestyle photography.\n* **Colors**: Bright Whites, Soft Sage gradients, Forest Green highlights, and organic grey text. \n* **Typography**: Elegant \"Inter\" sans-serif with tracked-out uppercase subheadings.\n* **Vibe**: Trustworthy, bright, fresh, and modern. Completely removes traditional \"stoner\" stigma.\n\n**Theme Option 3: Organic Botanical Store**\n* **Visual Direction**: Earthy and apothecary-like. Uses deeper natural textures and botanical illustrations. \n* **Colors**: Deep Emerald, Earthy Browns, and Warm Off-White (Cream).\n* **Typography**: Classic Serif headings (e.g., Playfair Display) paired with clean sans-body text.\n* **Vibe**: Holistic, grown-from-the-earth, organic, and artisanal. \n\n**Theme Option 4: Luxury Cannabis Boutique**\n* **Visual Direction**: Stark minimalism. Extreme use of negative space, thin lines, and very few elements on screen at once. Resembles a high-end fragrance or jewelry site.\n* **Colors**: Stark White, Onyx Black text, and singular Emerald Green buttons.\n* **Typography**: Ultra-thin luxury sans-serifs.\n* **Vibe**: Exclusive, expensive, and avant-garde.\n\n**Theme Option 5: Modern South African Lifestyle**\n* **Visual Direction**: High energy, vibrant, leaning into local Johannesburg street-culture while staying clean. \n* **Colors**: Crisp White with high-contrast Lime Green accents and bold charcoal text.\n* **Typography**: Heavy, bold display fonts.\n* **Vibe**: Energetic, community-driven, and fast-moving.\n\n---\n\n### Strategic Recommendation & Implementation: Theme 2\n\nI strongly recommend and have built **Theme Option 2 (Premium Wellness & Lifestyle)**. \n\nTo achieve the \"most professional cannabis lifestyle store in Johannesburg\" while maximizing sales conversion, the brand must immediately signal safety, quality, and approachability. Theme 2 perfectly straddles the line between luxury and accessible wellness without feeling cold (like Theme 1/4) or overly earthy (like Theme 3).\n\n### What I Built\n\nI have generated the fully functional, multi-page web application featuring this exact premium architecture and avoiding all dark/underground aesthetics:\n* **Premium Visual Identity**: Implemented a strict bright/white aesthetic heavily utilizing Soft Sage gradients, Forest Green typography, rounded e-commerce cards, and glassmorphism elements. \n* **Full-Page Architecture**: \n  * **Home**: Immersive hero lifestyle banner, professional corporate \'About\' segment, \'Why Choose Us\' feature blocks, curated featured cards, custom \'Cannabis Education\', and testimonials.\n  * **Products**: Complex filtering logic (Categories, Search) laid over a beautiful, shadow-hover grid matching modern D2C standards. \n  * **About & Contact**: Deep corporate storytelling pages and a full contact center including operation hours and interactive forms.\n* **WhatsApp Checkout Engine**: Built a full active React Context shopping cart that dynamically calculates totals, allows quantity updates, and compiles the entire order into a structured text message that seamlessly routes straight to the `+2711...` WhatsApp line on checkout."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 692204288
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
